decks.notes: This deck focuses on controlling the game using a combination of powerful elemental creatures and disruptive spells. It aims to generate value through cards like Risen Reef and Omnath, Locus of Creation, while using counterspells, removal, and cards like Teferi, Time Raveler to disrupt the opponent's game plan. With the help of Yorion, Sky Nomad as a companion, the deck can generate even more value by blinking its creatures and permanents. Additionally, the mana base is carefully crafted to support the various color requirements of the deck's spells.

The main focus of this deck is to control the game through countering spells, drawing cards, and generating value with cards like Wrenn and Six and Shark Typhoon. The deck aims to stall the game until it can establish a strong board presence with Wilderness Reclamation, allowing it to generate mana and cast powerful spells like Nexus of Fate and Expansion / Explosion. Additionally, the deck utilizes various lands to fix its mana base and provide additional utility. Overall, the strategy revolves around maintaining control of the game and outvaluing the opponent.

Utilizing powerful Tron lands to quickly ramp into mana and play large threats, this Control deck focuses on disrupting opponents with removal and graveyard hate while ultimately winning the game with devastating planeswalkers and Eldrazi creatures. The key strategy is to assemble UrzaTron as quickly as possible to overwhelm opponents with powerful threats and control elements, creating a strong board presence and dominating the late game. By combining efficient ramp, removal, and game-winning threats, this deck aims to outvalue and outlast opponents in a grindy game of attrition.
